I come here fairly frequently, probably once a month or so for over two years. I am not exaggerating when I say they get my order wrong about 60% of the time. No matter how many times I restate my order, they cannot get it. I think it's a problem with the computer system maybe? The people are generally friendly about fixing my order (although not always). A few examples. I often ask for a small bowl but am given a large bowl or a small burrito. One time they charged me for one  burrito but accidentally made me two burritos. Sometimes there's no salsa when I ask for salsa. Today the cashier (who was training another cashier) told me that salsa comes automatically so don't ask for it, and then there was not salsa on my bowl. They also gave me chicken when I asked for fish. I know I should stop going but the food itself is fine and there aren't many good food options in this area. I wish Cal Tort would just figure this out.
